<TITLE> Toyota to pay $16.4 million US fine </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 DETROIT, Apr 19 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Toyota Motor Corp has agreed to pay a record $16.4 million (10.7 million pound) fine to US safety regulators for delaying a massive recall over defective accelerator pedals, the regulator said on Monday. "By failing to report known safety problems as it is required to do under the law, Toyota put consumers at risk," Transportation Department Secretary Ray LaHood said in a statement. "I am pleased that Toyota has accepted responsibility for violating its legal obligations to report any defects promptly," LaHood said. The regulator continues to review Toyota's statements and more than 120,000 pages of Toyota documents to determine whether the world's largest automaker has complied with all its disclosure obligations, LaHood said. The $16.4 million civil penalty against Toyota is the maximum allowed by US law and the largest that the US Department of Transportation had ever sou
